What are Autoflowering seeds?

Autoflowering seeds are cannabis seeds that automatically transition from the vegetative stage to the flowering stage without relying on changes in light cycles. Unlike photoperiod strains, autoflower cannabis seeds begin flowering based on age, typically within 2–4 weeks of germination.

Popular among beginner and experienced growers alike, autoflower seeds are known for their fast growth, compact size, and ability to thrive in a variety of environments — including indoor, outdoor, and small spaces.

If you’re looking for easy-to-grow cannabis seeds with rapid harvest times, autoflowering seeds UK are an ideal choice. Their resilience, high yield potential, and discreet growth patterns make them a favourite for seed collectors and growers across the UK and beyond.

While autoflowering seeds are all about speed and simplicity, some growers still love the control and potency of classic photoperiod genetics. Explore our full Tastebudz Classic Strains collection — featuring time-tested favourites with rich terpene profiles and high yield potential.

What are Photoperiod Seeds?

Photoperiod seeds are cannabis seeds that rely on changes in the light cycle to trigger the flowering stage. Unlike autoflowering seeds, photoperiod cannabis seeds require a specific light-to-dark ratio — typically 12 hours of light and 12 hours of darkness — to initiate flowering.

Favoured by experienced growers, photoperiod strains offer greater control over plant size, growth cycles, and yield potential. With careful cultivation, photoperiod cannabis seeds can produce higher THC levels, larger buds, and customisable harvests.

If you’re looking for high-performance cannabis genetics and want full control over flowering timing, photoperiod seeds UK are a top choice for skilled cultivators and cannabis seed collectors.
